1. Creaci dun objecte Phyloseq

physeq <- qza_to_phyloseq(
  features = "qiime2/clustered/table-or-90.qza",
  tree = "qiime2/alignment/rooted-tree.qza",
  taxonomy = "qiime2/tax_class/table_tax_sklearn.qza",
  metadata = "mice_data/mice_metadata.tsv"
)

physeq

Es mostra les corves de rarefacci de les mostres sense pre-processat, que no permeten veure la riquesa total de cadascuna de les mostres.

otu_rare = as.data.frame(t(otu_table(physeq)))

Com podem veure, no podem arribar a coneixer la riquesa total de les mostres, pel que caldr filtrar-les per veure si millorem aquest parmetre.

2. Filtratge de les mostres

En primer lloc, eliminem els taxons que no corresponen a microorganismes, com cloroplasts, mitocondries i eucariotes.

filterPhyla <- c("Chloroplast", "Mitochondria", "d__Eukaryota")
physeq1 <- subset_taxa(physeq, !Kingdom %in% filterPhyla)
physeq1 <- subset_taxa(physeq1, !Phylum %in% filterPhyla)
physeq1 <- subset_taxa(physeq1, !Class %in% filterPhyla)
physeq1 <- subset_taxa(physeq1, !Order %in% filterPhyla)
physeq1 <- subset_taxa(physeq1, !Family %in% filterPhyla)
physeq1 <- subset_taxa(physeq1, !Genus %in% filterPhyla)
physeq1

A ms, en formar OTUs es tendeix a sobreestimar la riquesa duna mostra, s a dir el nombre dunitats taxonmiques en una mostra. Per evitar falsos positius, farem un filtratge segons prevalncia.

# Calculem prevalncies
prev = apply(X = otu_table(physeq1),
               MARGIN = ifelse(taxa_are_rows(physeq1), yes = 1, no = 2),
               FUN = function(x){sum(x > 0)})

# Creem un dataframe amb les prevalences, abundncies i tamb afegim les taxonomies
prevdf = data.frame(Prevalence = prev,
                    TotalAbundance = taxa_sums(physeq1),
                    tax_table(physeq1))

# Mostrem la taula
prev_physeq1 <- plyr::ddply(prevdf, "Phylum", function(df1){cbind(mean(df1$Prevalence),sum(df1$Prevalence))})

3. Mesura de la riquesa: alfa-diversistat

Mesurem lalfa-diversitat en funci del genotip. Ho farem amb els ndex Observed, Chao1, ACE, Shannon i Simpson. A ms, inclourem el p-valor que sobt amb cada ndex.

En funci del genotip

# Establim les mesures d'alfa-diversitat
alpha_means = c("Observed", "Chao1", "ACE", "Shannon", "Simpson")

# Calculem les mtriques d'alfa-diversitat, i ho combinem amb les metadades.
alpha_div <- estimate_richness(physeq3, measures = alpha_means)
metadata <- as.data.frame(sample_data(physeq3)) 
rownames(alpha_div) <- sub("^X", "", rownames(alpha_div))
combined_data <- cbind(alpha_div, metadata)

# Apliquem el test wilcoxon a totes les mtriques d'alfa-diversitat
alpha_div_genotype <- lapply(alpha_means, function(measure) {
  group_WT <- combined_data[[measure]][combined_data$Genotype == "WT"]
  group_KO <- combined_data[[measure]][combined_data$Genotype == "KO"]
  wilcox.test(group_WT, group_KO, exact = FALSE)
})

# Mostrem l'estadstic i p-valor del test per cada mtrica
alpha_div_genotype_df <- data.frame(
  Measure = alpha_means, 
  p_value = sapply(alpha_div_genotype, function(test) test$p.value),
  Statistic = sapply(alpha_div_genotype, function(test) test$statistic)
)
alpha_div_genotype_df
# Representem l'alpha-diversitat segons genotip
plot_richness(physeq3, color = "Genotype", "Genotype", measures = alpha_means) + 
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill = Genotype), alpha=0.1) +
  stat_compare_means(aes(label = ..p.signif..), method = "wilcox.test", comparisons = list(c("WT", "KO")), label = "p.format") +
  ggtitle("Alpha-diversity - Genotype")

ggsave("alfa-div_genotype.jpeg", device = "jpeg", path = "R_analysis", height = 8, width = 7)

En funci de laparici de tumor, per cada genotip

# Primer haurem de dividir l'objecte phyloseq segons el genotip de cadascun
physeq.WT = subset_samples(physeq3, Genotype == "WT")
physeq.KO = subset_samples(physeq3, Genotype == "KO")

# Per aplicar els tests tamb es filtren les dades d'alpha_div
subset_WT <- combined_data[combined_data$Genotype == "WT", ]
subset_KO <- combined_data[combined_data$Genotype == "KO", ]

# Alpha-diversitat segons l'aparici o no de tumor - WT
# Aplicaci test de Wilcoxon
alpha_div_tumorWT <- lapply(alpha_means, function(measure) {
  group_WT_HCC <- subset_WT[[measure]][subset_WT$HCC..YES.NO. == "YES"]
  group_WT_noHCC <- combined_data[[measure]][subset_WT$HCC..YES.NO. == "NO"]
  wilcox.test(group_WT_HCC, group_WT_noHCC, exact = FALSE)
})

# Mostrem l'estadstic i p-valor del test per cada mtrica
alpha_div_HCC_WT_df <- data.frame(
  Measure = alpha_means, 
  p_value = sapply(alpha_div_tumorWT, function(test) test$p.value),
  Statistic = sapply(alpha_div_tumorWT, function(test) test$statistic)
)
alpha_div_HCC_WT_df
# Representaci grfica
plot_richness(physeq.WT, color = "HCC..YES.NO.", "HCC..YES.NO.", measures = alpha_means) + 
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill = HCC..YES.NO.), alpha=0.1) +
  stat_compare_means(aes(label = ..p.signif..), method = "wilcox.test", comparisons = list(c("YES", "NO")), label = "p.format") +
  ggtitle("Alpha-diversity - HCC, WT group")

ggsave("alfa-div_WT.jpeg", device = "jpeg", path = "R_analysis", height = 8, width = 7)
# Alpha-diversitat segons l'aparici o no de tumor - KO
# Aplicaci test de Wilcoxon
alpha_div_tumorKO <- lapply(alpha_means, function(measure) {
  group_KO_HCC <- subset_WT[[measure]][subset_KO$HCC..YES.NO. == "YES"]
  group_KO_noHCC <- combined_data[[measure]][subset_KO$HCC..YES.NO. == "NO"]
  wilcox.test(group_KO_HCC, group_KO_noHCC, exact = FALSE)
})

# Mostrem l'estadstic i p-valor del test per cada mtrica
alpha_div_HCC_KO_df <- data.frame(
  Measure = alpha_means, 
  p_value = sapply(alpha_div_tumorKO, function(test) test$p.value),
  Statistic = sapply(alpha_div_tumorKO, function(test) test$statistic)
)
alpha_div_HCC_KO_df
# Representaci grfica
plot_richness(physeq.KO, color = "HCC..YES.NO.", "HCC..YES.NO.", measures = alpha_means) + 
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill = HCC..YES.NO.), alpha=0.1) +
  stat_compare_means(aes(label = ..p.signif..), method = "wilcox.test", comparisons = list(c("YES", "NO")), label = "p.format") +
  ggtitle("Alfa-diversity - HCC, KO group")

ggsave("alfa-div_KO.jpeg", device = "jpeg", path = "R_analysis",  height = 8, width = 7)
# Alpha-diversitat segons l'aparici o no de tumor - TOTAL
# Aplicaci test de Wilcoxon
alpha_div_tumor <- lapply(alpha_means, function(measure) {
  group_YES <- combined_data[[measure]][combined_data$HCC..YES.NO. == "YES"]
  group_NO <- combined_data[[measure]][combined_data$HCC..YES.NO. == "NO"]
  wilcox.test(group_YES, group_NO, exact = FALSE)
})

# Mostrem l'estadstic i p-valor del test per cada mtrica

  Measure = alpha_means,

4. Mesura de la riquesa: beta-diversitat

Per calcular la beta-diversitat, es fan servir dues distncies diferents: unifrac i bray.

En primer lloc, utilitzem el test PERMANOVA basat en la matriu de distncies unifrac i bray, en aquest cas en funci del genotip:

# Calculem la matriu de distncies unifrac
physeq.unifrac <- phyloseq::distance(physeq3, method= "unifrac")

# Test PERMANOVA - Genotype
permanova_unifrac_genotype <- adonis2(physeq.unifrac ~ Genotype, data = data.frame(sample_data(physeq3)), permutations= 999)
Pvalue_permanova_unifrac_genotype <- paste0("PERMANOVA p = ", signif(permanova_unifrac_genotype$`Pr(>F)`[1]))
# Calculem la matriu de distncies bray
physeq.bray <- phyloseq::distance(physeq3, method= "bray")

# Test PERMANOVA - Genotype
permanova_bray_genotype <- adonis2(physeq.bray ~ Genotype, data = data.frame(sample_data(physeq3)), permutations= 999)
Pvalue_permanova_bray_genotype <- paste0("PERMANOVA p = ", signif(permanova_bray_genotype$`Pr(>F)`[1]))
# Calculem matriu de distncia Unifrac
physeq3.mds.unifrac <- ordinate(physeq3, method = "MDS", distance = "unifrac")
evalues_unifrac <- physeq3.mds.unifrac$values$Eigenvalues

# Grfic d'ordenades per distncia Unifrac
ordinates_unifrac_genotype <- plot_ordination(physeq3, physeq3.mds.unifrac, color = "Genotype") +
  labs(col = "Genotype") +
  coord_fixed(sqrt(evalues_unifrac[2]/ evalues_unifrac[1])) +
  stat_ellipse() +
  annotate("text", x = -0.9, y = 0.6, label = Pvalue_permanova_unifrac_genotype, hjust = 0, size = 3)
ordinates_unifrac_genotype

ggsave("beta-div_Genotype_unifrac.jpeg", device = "jpeg", path = "R_analysis",  height = 8, width = 7)
  
# Clcul matriu de distncia Bray-Curtis
physeq3.mds.bray <- ordinate(physeq3, method = "MDS", distance = "bray")
evalues_bray <- physeq3.mds.bray$values$Eigenvalues

# Grfic d'ordenades per distncia Bray-Curtis
ordinates_bray_genotype <- plot_ordination(physeq3, physeq3.mds.bray, color = "Genotype") +
  labs(col = "Genotype") +
  coord_fixed(sqrt(evalues_bray[2]/ evalues_bray[1])) +
  stat_ellipse() +
  annotate("text", x = -0.9, y = 0.8, label = Pvalue_permanova_bray_genotype, hjust = 0, size = 3)
ordinates_bray_genotype

ggsave("beta-div_Genotype_bray.jpeg", device = "jpeg", path = "R_analysis",  height = 8, width = 7)

ordinates_bray_KO.HCC <- plot_ordination(physeq.KO, physeqKO.mds.bray, color = "HCC..YES.NO.") +
  labs(col = "HCC..YES.NO.") +
  coord_fixed(sqrt(evalues_bray[2]/ evalues_bray[1])) +
  stat_ellipse() +
  annotate("text", x = -0.9, y = 1.1, label = Pvalue_permanova_bray_KO.HCC, hjust = 0, size = 3) +
  ggtitle("Beta-diversity [Bray] - HCC, KO group")

6. Anlisi dabundncia diferencial

Per determinar quins taxons estan ms representats en una condici, es fa servir el mateix procs que en lanlisi dexpressi diferencial de gens (ie RNA-seq). Per aix, es fa servir el paquet DESeq2.

En funci del genotip

Primer generem un objecte DESeq. Amb la funci, es normalitza la mida de les mostres (num de reads), i la variabilitat - per default es realitza amb el test paramtric de correcci Benjamini-Hochberg. A ms, calculem les mitjanes geomtriques abans de estimar la mida dels factors.

physeq_ddseq = phyloseq_to_deseq2(physeq3, ~Genotype)
## converting counts to integer mode
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): some variables in
## design formula are characters, converting to factors
# Normalitzem les mostres
gm_mean = function(x, na.rm=TRUE){
    exp(sum(log(x[x > 0]), na.rm=na.rm) / length(x))
}
geoMeans = apply(counts(physeq_ddseq), 1, gm_mean)
physeq_ddseq = estimateSizeFactors(physeq_ddseq, geoMeans = geoMeans)
physeq_ddseq = DESeq(physeq_ddseq, fitType = "local")
## using pre-existing size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 140 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
